qas.question: What were people protesting in Kiev during the last part of February?
Who did the protesters want to resign?
Who visited the Ukraine while the protests were taking place?
How many people attended the service in Lviv?

context: In late February, large public rallies took place in Kiev to protest the <a0_0>election laws<a0_0/>, on the eve of the March 26 elections to the USSR Congress of People's Deputies, and to call for the resignation of the first secretary of the Communist Party of Ukraine, <a1_0>Volodymyr Scherbytsky<a1_0/>, lampooned as "<a2_0>the mastodon of stagnation<a2_0/>." The demonstrations coincided with a visit to Ukraine by Soviet President <a3_0>Gorbachev<a3_0/>. On February 26, 1989, <a4_0>between 20,000 and 30,000<a4_0/> people participated in an unsanctioned ecumenical memorial service in Lviv, marking the anniversary of the death of 19th Century Ukrainian artist and nationalist Taras Shevchenko.
